name:                allot
stack:               ( n -- )
return stack:        ( -- )
string stack:        ( -- )
contexts:            stateless
category:            memory, allocation

decription:          reserves n cells of memory, beginning at the address
                     produced by executing here.
                     negative n can be used to deallocate memory, but only
                     if deallocated memory block is the last block allocated.

standard:            yes
                     https://forth-standard.org/standard/core/ALLOT
